<br>
It all began about 30 hours ago, when I conferred with my fellow Bardic collegues and decided I was going for it.  It, was the Mask of Deception; to those not Bard or Rogue the distinction would be lost on you but in OUR world it is a sign of a very good Bard or Rogue.  Some hours later sets me on the road of deception of the Mask of Deception; getting to the the Mask was easier said than done.  Death came easily when the Mask is held by those of at least the 35th Season and higher.  Let's say this the ghoul assassin, himself, gave a 60th season Paladin experience, very little, but still.  Many deaths occured in the reaching of the Mask, some by myself and some by others.  Some hours later, after being physically revolted by the Guk itself, a kind, noble Paladin comes to my aid.  He unfortunately didn't know what he was getting into. . .for 18 hours he and I sat waiting for the ghoul assassin, who only appeared 3 times in 18 hours.  How easy they said it was, my Bardic friends.  Ha, but this kind Paladin sat with me.  Got me my Mask.  So, this ends the tale, but as you can see the deception of this Mask started even before I had laid eyes upon it.  And I think to myself, how very sad.  Here is the end of the tale.<br>
The moral(s) of the story is: don't believe others to closely, never go to Guk, never fight in Guk, never live in Guk temeporary.  Those some good morals, I guess.  You can take your own. <p><img src="http://www.wynd-haven.com/Images/ToirReasaSig.jpg">
